name: A1AT Deficiency
symptoms: Wheezing or whistling sounds when you breathe
A fast heartbeat when you stand up

name: AAT
symptoms: Wheezing or whistling sounds when you breathe
A fast heartbeat when you stand up

name: AAT Deficiency
symptoms: Wheezing or whistling sounds when you breathe
A fast heartbeat when you stand up

name: Abercrombie Syndrome
symptoms: Tingling and numbness in legs and feet

name: Abscessed Tooth
symptoms: Sensitivity to hot or cold temperatures
A bad odor when you chew with that tooth
A rush of fluid in your mouth that's salty, bad-tasting, or foul-smelling, followed by an easing of your pain. That means your abscess has ruptured.

name: Absence of Menstruation, Primary
symptoms: More hair growth on your face
A milky discharge from your nipples

name: Achalasia
symptoms: Food coming back up into the throat
Pneumonia from breathing food into the lungs

name: Achilles Tendon Problems
symptoms: Tight Achilles tendon in the morning
Stiffness or pain along your Achilles tendon
Pain that gets worse with activity
Heel pain when you wear shoes
Severe pain the day after physical activity
Swelling that doesn't go away, or gets better then returns

name: Acromegaly
symptoms: Achy joints, possibly leading to arthritis
Sweating a lot with body odor
Snoring and sleep apnea, a breathing problem that happens during sleep
Tingling or pain in fingers (carpal tunnel syndrome)
Changes in menstrual cycle and breast discharge in women

name: Age-Related Macular Degeneration
symptoms: Worse or less clear vision. Your vision might be blurry, and it may be hard to read fine print, drive, or recognize faces.
Dark, blurry areas in the center of your vision

name: Agnogenic Myeloid Metaplasia (AMM)
symptoms: Fatigue, weakness, shortness of breath, or pale skin because of a low number of red blood cells (anemia)
Frequent infections because of a low white blood cell count (neutropenia)
Easy bleeding or bruising because of a lack of platelets in your blood (thrombocytopenia)
Bleeding in your stomach or esophagus
High blood pressure in the vein from your spleen to your liver (portal hypertension)
